==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glyoxaline
<hw>Gly*ox"a*line</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A white, crystalline, organic base, <chform>C3H4N2</chform>,
produced by the action of ammonia on glyoxal, and forming the origin of
a large class of derivatives hence, any one of the series of which
glyoxaline is a type; -- called also
<altname>oxaline</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glyoxime</ent>⟦br⟧
